00:29:49.750 --> 00:29:52.870
what we did to increase
engagement and tell that story?

00:29:52.870 --> 00:29:55.330
So I think this is
the rookie mistake.

00:29:55.330 --> 00:29:59.380
It's just too much gaming
of the investor community

00:29:59.380 --> 00:30:01.180
and trying to figure
out how to hack it.

00:30:01.180 --> 00:30:02.740
And what are they thinking?

00:30:02.740 --> 00:30:04.676
It's pretty simple
what they're thinking.

00:30:04.676 --> 00:30:07.200
Does this person
have the ability

00:30:07.200 --> 00:30:12.189
to build a team that can build
a product that delights users?

00:30:12.189 --> 00:30:13.980
And if they can get
that product to market,

00:30:13.980 --> 00:30:16.740
you've built that credibility.

00:30:16.740 --> 00:30:19.200
And to think it's going to
happen after one meeting is

00:30:19.200 --> 00:30:20.340
probably silly.

00:30:20.340 --> 00:30:22.150
Like it usually
happens over five,

00:30:22.150 --> 00:30:24.440
six, seven meetings
an email update.

00:30:24.440 --> 00:30:29.340
So I'm so pro this monthly
update that I require it

00:30:29.340 --> 00:30:32.232
for my investments, because
the first 100 investments

00:30:32.232 --> 00:30:34.440
I did, I didn't require them
to send monthly updates.

00:30:34.440 --> 00:30:37.467
Now, in my legal documents,
I require a monthly update.

00:30:37.467 --> 00:30:39.300
That starts with the
most important metrics.

00:30:39.300 --> 00:30:41.454
How many months of
run we need to have,

00:30:41.454 --> 00:30:42.870
how much cash is
left in the bank,

00:30:42.870 --> 00:30:44.661
when do we need to
raise money next, what's

00:30:44.661 --> 00:30:47.250
the revenue, what's
the user engagement.

00:30:47.250 --> 00:30:49.950
And so I've been making
this a requirement,

00:30:49.950 --> 00:30:53.220
because so many founders
don't send these updates.

00:30:53.220 --> 00:30:55.170
And then they don't
have the opportunity

00:30:55.170 --> 00:30:57.120
