back in the company.

01:02:05.770 --> 01:02:08.640
So because those big five are
so competitive with startups now

01:02:08.640 --> 01:02:11.670
and aware of the
startup ecosystem,

01:02:11.670 --> 01:02:13.320
I think a clean break
is the wisest way

01:02:13.320 --> 01:02:16.630
to go if you want to
raise some serious people.

01:02:16.630 --> 01:02:20.550
And most companies
pivot here and there.

01:02:20.550 --> 01:02:24.510
The term pivot used to mean
taking what you've learned

01:02:24.510 --> 01:02:27.290
and changing your
direction slightly.

01:02:27.290 --> 01:02:30.840
One foot staying where it is,
and then you're moving around.

01:02:30.840 --> 01:02:33.930
The word pivot somehow meant
dropping the existing idea

01:02:33.930 --> 01:02:36.500
and coming up with a
completely different idea.

01:02:36.500 --> 01:02:39.330
That's not the term
pivot as we all use it.

01:02:39.330 --> 01:02:40.830
But people are like,
we're pivoting.

01:02:40.830 --> 01:02:44.455
And pivoting now in Silicon
Valley means this failed.

01:02:44.455 --> 01:02:45.330
Now we're doing this.

01:02:45.330 --> 01:02:47.100
That's not pivoting.

01:02:47.100 --> 01:02:50.580
Pivoting is we were
going to go and do

01:02:50.580 --> 01:02:52.770
video for the enterprise.

01:02:52.770 --> 01:02:55.890
But then we found this
new class of prosumers.

01:02:55.890 --> 01:02:58.650
So we're kind of going
to make it prosumerwear.

01:02:58.650 --> 01:03:01.080
It's free for most people and
paid for the elite people,

01:03:01.080 --> 01:03:02.913
but it's not going to
be an enterprise video

01:03:02.913 --> 01:03:05.857
solution anymore, because
we realize the enterprise,

01:03:05.857 --> 01:03:07.440
you know, they like
to roll their own.

01:03:07.440 --> 01:03:08.220
That would be a pivot.

01:03:08.220 --> 01:03:09.750
You're staying in
the same vertical.

01:03:09.750 --> 01:03:11.708
You're shifting the
customer base a little bit.

01:03:11.708 --> 01:03:13.990
But the product and everything
is in the same zone.

01:03:13.990 --> 01:03:16.560
So that happens in
almost every company

01:03:16.560 --> 01:03:17.714
where you learn as you go.

01:03:17.714 --> 01:03:18.630
Very few get it right.

01:03:18.630 --> 01:03:23.160
In fact, if you look at
Uber, is going into ride

01:03:23.160 --> 01:03:25.830
sharing an Uber pool, a pivot?

01:03:25.830 --> 01:03:29.100
No, but maybe in the
classic term it was.

01:03:29.100 --> 01:03:30.690
We started with black cars--

01:03:30.690 --> 01:03:32.670
Lincoln Town Cars,
expensive cars.

01:03:32.670 --> 01:03:34.560
We pivoted to ride sharing.

01:03:34.560 --> 01:03:35.580
We added it.

01:03:35.580 --> 01:03:40.260
You know, we moved our
focus over a bit to it.

01:03:40.260 --> 01:03:44.310
So I think it depends on which
definition of pivot you're

01:03:44.310 --> 01:03:46.480
going with.

01:03:46.480 --> 01:03:50.100
